# Knotwork — the lead: an UN-instrument. Every acoustic instrument is
# brightest at the attack and mellows; this voice is built backwards —
# NEGATIVE filter envelope: the note lands dark and BLOOMS into bright
# sustain over 350 ms. Nothing struck, blown, or bowed does that, so
# the ear files it as "synthesizer", full stop. Sync at +3 (a smeared
# non-formant color, not the +7 brass vowel), ring 0.3 for locked
# inharmonic glint, PWM churn and a slow filter wobble so the spectrum
# never repeats. No pluck, no horn, no string, no piano.
waveform 2
osc2_wave 1
osc2_pitch 3
osc2_level 0.5
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 5
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 0.7
osc_fm 0.08
sync 1
ring 0.3
glide 0
pulse_width 0.3
attack 0.04
decay 0.5
sustain 0.75
release 0.4
filter_env -1.4
filter_attack 0.005
filter_decay 0.35
filter_sustain 0.15
filter_release 0.3
cutoff 2600
resonance 0.7
drive 1.8
saturation 1.05
hpf 120
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.12
lfo_rate 0.8
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0.12
lfo_pwm 0.2
